text: Petrus "Peter" Wilhelmus Frederikus Nottet (born 23 September 1944) is a Dutch speed skater. He competed in the 1964 Winter Olympics and in the 1968 Winter Olympics.Peter Nottet. sports-reference.com In 1964 he finished 34th in the 5000 metres event. Four years later he won the bronze medal in the 5000 metres competition. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:Living people Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the Netherlands Category:Dutch speed skaters Category:Sportspeople from The Hague
